  <prompt>
    Create a static utility class DesktopUrlBuilder that generates Office desktop protocol URLs 
    (ms-word:, ms-excel:, ms-powerpoint:) from SharePoint Embedded web URLs. The utility must 
    map MIME types to protocol schemes and return null for unsupported types. Follow ADR-010 
    DI Minimalism by using static methods.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Expert in C# and .NET 8. Follow ADRs strictly. 
    Prefer minimal abstractions per ADR-010.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A working DesktopUrlBuilder.cs utility class with static method FromMime(webUrl, mimeType) 
    that returns correctly formatted protocol URLs, with unit tests achieving full coverage 
    of all mappings and edge cases.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      The FileViewer PCF currently opens documents in embedded edit mode, which is slow and 
      confusing. We're replacing this with "Open in Desktop" functionality that uses Office 
      protocol handlers (ms-word:ofe|u|{url}). This utility provides the URL transformation 
      logic that the BFF endpoint will use.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/shared/Spaarke.SharePointEmbedded/Utilities/DesktopUrlBuilder.cs (create)</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Spaarke.SharePointEmbedded.Tests/DesktopUrlBuilderTests.cs (create)</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-fileviewer-enhancements-1/spec.md (reference)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">Use static methods - no DI registration needed for pure functions</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">Keep utility focused and minimal - single responsibility</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Must handle null/empty inputs gracefully (return null)</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Must support Word, Excel, and PowerPoint MIME types</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-010-di-minimalism.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-001-minimal-api-and-workers.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-fileviewer-enhancements-1/spec.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Office Protocol URL" location="spec.md Section 5.1">
        Format: ms-{app}:ofe|u|{encoded-web-url}
        - ms-word: for .docx (application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document)
        - ms-excel: for .xlsx (application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet)
        - ms-powerpoint: for .pptx (application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.presentationml.presentation)
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Create Utilities folder in src/shared/Spaarke.SharePointEmbedded/ if missing</step>
    <step order="2">Create DesktopUrlBuilder.cs with static class definition and XML documentation</step>
    <step order="3">Implement private static dictionary mapping MIME types to protocol schemes</step>
    <step order="4">Implement public static FromMime(string webUrl, string mimeType) method</step>
    <step order="5">Add null/empty handling - return null for invalid inputs</step>
    <step order="6">Add URL encoding for the webUrl parameter</step>
    <step order="7">Create test file DesktopUrlBuilderTests.cs in tests/unit/</step>
    <step order="8">Write tests for Word MIME type mapping</step>
    <step order="9">Write tests for Excel MIME type mapping</step>
    <step order="10">Write tests for PowerPoint MIME type mapping</step>
    <step order="11">Write tests for unsupported MIME types (returns null)</step>
    <step order="12">Write tests for null/empty webUrl (returns null)</step>
    <step order="13">Run dotnet build and verify no errors</step>
    <step order="14">Run dotnet test and verify all tests pass</step>
    <step order="15">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change this task's status from ðŸ”² to âœ…</step>
